metadata.title: Failure handlers TypeScript only
metadata.content:
Failure handlers TypeScript only
If your function exhausts all of its retries, it will be marked as "Failed." You can handle this circumstance by either providing an
[```
onFailure/on_failure
```](\docs\reference\functions\handling-failures)
handler when defining your function, or by listening for the
[```
inngest/function.failed
```](\docs\reference\system-events\inngest-function-failed)
system event.
The first approach is function-specific, while the second covers all function failures in a given Inngest environment.
